    "attributes": {
        "action": "Urge China to allow direct flights between UK and China to resume",
        "additional_details": "Since December 2020 China has banned direct flights from the UK to the Chinese mainland, making it extremely difficult and expensive for Chinese citizens and residents to return home, and vice versa.\r\n\r\nSome Chinese and UK citizens and residents, particularly students, are being left stranded in each other\u2019s countries as the only available flight routes are so expensive and uncertain.\r\n\r\nThe situation is causing tremendous anxiety to many. Families have been separated, visas overstayed, jobs have been lost, and savings have been wiped out by the cost of extended stays abroad and expensive flights home. Not to mention the financial blow to the UK tourism industry and universities from losing Chinese students.",
        "background": "We are asking the Government to seek to negotiate with the Chinese Government for the resumption of direct flights between the UK and China. ",
